ENCFF000ZVD	-	-	/libraries/ENCLB197JDY/	97c5019479b18da8739b02190c668d36	2011-01-27T00:00:00.000000+00:00	23817388	36	released	/biosamples/ENCBS919IGK/	/genetic-modifications/ENCGM078PYN/	/biosample-types/cell_line_EFO_0002067/	K562	/targets/JUND-human/	-	insertion	tagging	eGFP	/labs/kevin-white/	Recombineering is used for tagging cassettes at either the N or C terminus of the protein. The N-terminal cassette has a dual eukaryotic-prokaryotic promoter (PGK-gb2) driving a neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene within an artificial intron inside the tag coding sequence. The selection cassette is flanked by two loxP sites and can be permanently removed by Cre Recombinase-mediated excision. The C-terminal cassette contains the sequence encoding the tag followed by an internal ribosome entry site (IRES) in front of the neomycin resistance gene. In addition, a short bacterial promoter (Gb3) drives the expression of the neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene in E. coli.

ENCFF000ZUQ	-	-	/libraries/ENCLB218GPE/	b06f28a6ced1a49d3503cb5bd76d31bb	2011-01-27T00:00:00.000000+00:00	22269628	36	released	/biosamples/ENCBS775URE/	/genetic-modifications/ENCGM227XVM/	/biosample-types/cell_line_EFO_0002067/	K562	/targets/JUNB-human/	-	insertion	tagging	eGFP	/labs/kevin-white/	Recombineering is used for tagging cassettes at either the N or C terminus of the protein. The N-terminal cassette has a dual eukaryotic-prokaryotic promoter (PGK-gb2) driving a neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene within an artificial intron inside the tag coding sequence. The selection cassette is flanked by two loxP sites and can be permanently removed by Cre Recombinase-mediated excision. The C-terminal cassette contains the sequence encoding the tag followed by an internal ribosome entry site (IRES) in front of the neomycin resistance gene. In addition, a short bacterial promoter (Gb3) drives the expression of the neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene in E. coli.

ENCFF000ZVF	-	-	/libraries/ENCLB796WKO/	1fcb7812e8107875b334d23c6251cde2	2011-01-27T00:00:00.000000+00:00	26356734	36	released	/biosamples/ENCBS715EUG/	/genetic-modifications/ENCGM166JET/	/biosample-types/cell_line_EFO_0002067/	K562	/targets/NR4A1-human/	-	insertion	tagging	eGFP	/labs/kevin-white/	Recombineering is used for tagging cassettes at either the N or C terminus of the protein. The N-terminal cassette has a dual eukaryotic-prokaryotic promoter (PGK-gb2) driving a neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene within an artificial intron inside the tag coding sequence. The selection cassette is flanked by two loxP sites and can be permanently removed by Cre Recombinase-mediated excision. The C-terminal cassette contains the sequence encoding the tag followed by an internal ribosome entry site (IRES) in front of the neomycin resistance gene. In addition, a short bacterial promoter (Gb3) drives the expression of the neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene in E. coli.

ENCFF137CSB	-	-	/libraries/ENCLB036EBJ/	edd8a56308b64d84c6e296844b35feb8	2019-09-30T21:17:12.826316+00:00	29854912	75	released	/biosamples/ENCBS933WPT/	/genetic-modifications/ENCGM674JZD/	/biosample-types/cell_line_EFO_0001187/	HepG2	/targets/CEBPD-human/	CRISPR	insertion	tagging	3xFLAG	/labs/richard-myers/	ChIP-Seq on HepG2
ENCFF000ZUD	-	-	/libraries/ENCLB162RTZ/	570525d41fdb33981b63f962d0cbfaa1	2011-01-27T00:00:00.000000+00:00	16930378	36	released	/biosamples/ENCBS607WST/	/genetic-modifications/ENCGM452NGP/	/biosample-types/cell_line_EFO_0002067/	K562	/targets/FOS-human/	-	insertion	tagging	eGFP	/labs/kevin-white/	Recombineering is used for tagging cassettes at either the N or C terminus of the protein. The N-terminal cassette has a dual eukaryotic-prokaryotic promoter (PGK-gb2) driving a neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene within an artificial intron inside the tag coding sequence. The selection cassette is flanked by two loxP sites and can be permanently removed by Cre Recombinase-mediated excision. The C-terminal cassette contains the sequence encoding the tag followed by an internal ribosome entry site (IRES) in front of the neomycin resistance gene. In addition, a short bacterial promoter (Gb3) drives the expression of the neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene in E. coli.

ENCFF000ZUK	-	-	/libraries/ENCLB573LZS/	e8bb45c0bb2ea5d23e81d2f02a3d5baf	2011-01-27T00:00:00.000000+00:00	32026588	36	released	/biosamples/ENCBS903OXA/	/genetic-modifications/ENCGM551ILF/	/biosample-types/cell_line_EFO_0002067/	K562	/targets/GATA2-human/	-	insertion	tagging	eGFP	/labs/kevin-white/	Recombineering is used for tagging cassettes at either the N or C terminus of the protein. The N-terminal cassette has a dual eukaryotic-prokaryotic promoter (PGK-gb2) driving a neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene within an artificial intron inside the tag coding sequence. The selection cassette is flanked by two loxP sites and can be permanently removed by Cre Recombinase-mediated excision. The C-terminal cassette contains the sequence encoding the tag followed by an internal ribosome entry site (IRES) in front of the neomycin resistance gene. In addition, a short bacterial promoter (Gb3) drives the expression of the neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene in E. coli.

ENCFF000ZVE	-	-	/libraries/ENCLB300FOY/	7d03fb3f855bb949563e61199a0ca587	2011-01-27T00:00:00.000000+00:00	22780382	36	released	/biosamples/ENCBS875VQC/	/genetic-modifications/ENCGM166JET/	/biosample-types/cell_line_EFO_0002067/	K562	/targets/NR4A1-human/	-	insertion	tagging	eGFP	/labs/kevin-white/	Recombineering is used for tagging cassettes at either the N or C terminus of the protein. The N-terminal cassette has a dual eukaryotic-prokaryotic promoter (PGK-gb2) driving a neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene within an artificial intron inside the tag coding sequence. The selection cassette is flanked by two loxP sites and can be permanently removed by Cre Recombinase-mediated excision. The C-terminal cassette contains the sequence encoding the tag followed by an internal ribosome entry site (IRES) in front of the neomycin resistance gene. In addition, a short bacterial promoter (Gb3) drives the expression of the neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene in E. coli.

ENCFF000ZUB	-	-	/libraries/ENCLB049VVD/	1a7f744b33a6cbd77eb4f014f19e0677	2011-01-27T00:00:00.000000+00:00	26098735	36	released	/biosamples/ENCBS746ASY/	/genetic-modifications/ENCGM551ILF/	/biosample-types/cell_line_EFO_0002067/	K562	/targets/GATA2-human/	-	insertion	tagging	eGFP	/labs/kevin-white/	Recombineering is used for tagging cassettes at either the N or C terminus of the protein. The N-terminal cassette has a dual eukaryotic-prokaryotic promoter (PGK-gb2) driving a neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene within an artificial intron inside the tag coding sequence. The selection cassette is flanked by two loxP sites and can be permanently removed by Cre Recombinase-mediated excision. The C-terminal cassette contains the sequence encoding the tag followed by an internal ribosome entry site (IRES) in front of the neomycin resistance gene. In addition, a short bacterial promoter (Gb3) drives the expression of the neomycin-kanamycin resistance gene in E. coli.
